(7, 'document', 'text/html', 'FAQS', 'FAQS', 'FAQS', 'faqs', 'FAQS', 1, 0, 0, 3, 0, '', '<h2 class="dec">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div id="faqs">\r\n<h3>Are there any additional charges other than the initial purchase price?</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>No, the price you pay is for the package you choose and lasts for one year only. You will need to contact us if you wanted to extend beyond the year.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Do I get a free .co.uk or .com domain with my website?</h3>\r\n<div class="justifyright">\r\n<p>Your Free domain name will be an appendage of the ''weddingwebsiteuk.co.uk''.<br />So for instance if you want to have ''alex-and-jo'' the domain name would be ''weddingwebsitesuk.co.uk/alex-and-jo.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Can I have more space to enable me to have more photographs on my website?</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Yes we have 3 packages that should suffice for most people. The top package allows 1000MB of space. This equates to around 300+ photos if each photo is 3MB.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>I am concerned about any personal information on my website appearing on the serach engines,  can i prevent my site from appearing in a web search?</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Yes. You have the option to prevent search engines from indexing your website. You can also password protect teh entire site or individual pages.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>How can i make a suggestion for the website?</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Please contact suggestions@weddingwebsitesuk.co.uk</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>How can i report a problem?</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Please contact support@.co.uk. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>How many photos can i upload to my website?</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>It depends on the physical file size of each phonto. If each photo is 3MB (typical size) then the basic package of 200MB would allow for approximately 66 images. However your photos may only be 1MB each in which case you could have up to 200 photos with the basic package.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- /faq-styles -->\r\n<script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[\r\n	$(document).ready(function() {\r\n  $(''#faqs h3'').each(function() {\r\n    var tis = $(this), state = false, answer = tis.next(''div'').hide().css(''height'',''auto'').slideUp();\r\n    tis.click(function() {\r\n      state = !state;\r\n      answer.slideToggle(state);\r\n      tis.toggleClass(''active'',state);\r\n    });\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n// ]]></script>', 1, 2, 1, 1, 0, 1, 1299013700, 1, 1316692059, 0, 0, 0, 1299013680, 1, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'wedding', 1),
(8, 'document', 'text/html', 'Contact', 'Contact', 'Contact', 'contact', 'Contact', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '<h2 class="dec">We''re here to help</h2>\r\n<p>Couldn''t find an answer in our FAQ section or want to know more about The Weddimg Website Group?<br />Complete the form below and we''ll get back to you as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<form id="EmailForm" action="[[~[[*id]]]]" method="post">\r\n<fieldset>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><label for="cfName">Your name: <span class="invalidValue">[[+fi.error.name]]</span></label> <input id="cfName" class="text" name="name:required" type="text" value="[[+fi.name]]" /> </li>\r\n<li><label for="cfEmail">Your Email Address: <span class="invalidValue">[[+fi.error.email]]</span> </label><input id="cfEmail" class="text" name="email:required:email" type="text" value="[[+fi.email]]" /> </li>\r\n<li><label for="cfMessage">Message: <span class="invalidValue">[[+fi.error.message]]</span> </label><textarea id="cfMessage" cols="20" rows="4" name="message:required:stripTags">[[+fi.message]]</textarea> </li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</fieldset>\r\n <fieldset class="submit">\r\n <input id="cfContact" class="submit-buy" name="submitContact" type="submit" value="Send enquiry" /> \r\n</fieldset>\r\n</form>\r\n<div class="divider-690"> </div>', 1, 2, 8, 1, 0, 1, 1299013717, 1, 1316705554, 0, 0, 0, 1299013680, 1, 'Contact', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'wedding', 1),
