(36, 'document', 'text/html', 'Terms and Conditions', 'Terms and Conditions', 'Terms and Conditions', 'terms-and-conditions', 'Terms and Conditions', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '<h2 class="dec">The Wedding Website Group Terms and Conditions</h2>\r\n<p>This\r\n"Agreement" is a contract between each party ("User") who\r\naccesses TheWeddingWebsiteGroup.com site (the "Site") and the\r\nproprietor of the Site ("24 Seven Communications", a company having a\r\nplace of business in Leeds, UK) regarding access to, and use of, the Site. </p>\r\n<p>By\r\naccessing, or otherwise using, the Site, User agrees to be bound by this\r\nAgreement and acknowledges the consideration provided by The Wedding Website\r\nGroup in support of this Agreement, and particularly including the disclaimers,\r\nlimitation of liability and provisions related to prohibited conduct and\r\nremedies set-out herein.</p>\r\n<p>The\r\nWedding Website Group reserves the right to change this Agreement at its sole\r\ndiscretion by posting revisions on the Site. Continued accessing, or otherwise\r\nusing, the Site following any such revision(s) constitutes acceptance of the\r\nrevised Agreement.</p>\r\n<p>USER\r\nAGREES TO REVIEW THIS AGREEMENT AND ANY CHANGES THERETO REGULARLY ENOUGH DURING\r\nTHE PERIOD OF TIME IN WHICH SUCH USER ACCESSES THE SITE TO ENSURE THAT SUCH\r\nUSER REMAINS FAMILIAR AND IN COMPLIANCE WITH THIS AGREEMENT. Any User not\r\nagreeing with this Agreement or any changes to or revisions thereof must\r\nterminate access to, or other use of, the Site immediately.</p>\r\n<p><strong>1. Registration, Accounts and Passwords.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The\r\nWedding Website Group site includes a number of wedding related services\r\n("Services") such as personalisation, web hosting, and others helpful\r\ntools such as direction services, all made available after registration. A User\r\nagrees to provide accurate and current information for such registration, and\r\nto update such information completely and timely as needed. User agrees not to\r\ndeceive or obfuscate in making such registration.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2. Member Conduct</strong></p>\r\n<p>We\r\nrequire that every user of the Service, whether or not such user is a Member,\r\nagrees not to use this Service to upload, store, share or otherwise obtain\r\nProhibited Content. Generally, Prohibited Content includes (without limitation)\r\nany of the following types of Content: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>a.\r\n     Content we believe is abusive, deceptive, pornographic, obscene,\r\n     defamatory, slanderous, offensive, or otherwise inappropriate. </li>\r\n<li>b.\r\n     Copyrighted material that is used without the express permission of the\r\n     owner. </li>\r\n<li>c.\r\n     Content that violates or encroaches on the rights of others. </li>\r\n<li>d.\r\n     Content or other material that contains viruses, worms, corrupt files,\r\n     Trojan horses and other forms of corruptive code or any other content,\r\n     which may compromise the The Wedding Website Group Service. </li>\r\n<li>e.\r\n     Content that advocates illegal activity. </li>\r\n<li>f.\r\n     Content that harms minors in any way. </li>\r\n<li>g. Any\r\n     links to the above. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>3. Use of Site.</strong></p>\r\n<p>A\r\nUSER AGREES THAT SUCH USER SHALL USE THE SITE SOLELY FOR THE PURPOSES INTENDED,\r\nNAMELY, A WEB SITE FOR PERSONAL USE OR AS OTHERWISE REFLECTED ON THE SITE\r\nITSELF BY THE WEDDING WEBSITE GROUP, AND SHALL NOT USE THIS SITE FOR COPYING OF\r\nTHE SITE ITSELF OR ANY PORTION THEREOF OR ANY CONTENT OR MATERIAL ON IT OR\r\nABOUT IT, OR TO MAKE FALSE OR FRAUDULENT REPRESENTATIONS OR TO POST, PERFORM,\r\nOR OTHERWISE DISTRIBUTE OR KNOWINGLY ALLOW ANOTHER TO POST, PERFORM, OR OTHERWISE\r\nDISTRIBUTE, ANY UNAUTHORIZED MATERIAL OWNED BY ANOTHER INCLUDING INFORMATION IN\r\nANY FORM, MUSIC, SOFTWARE, PHOTOGRAPHS OR IMAGES, FACSIMILES OR OTHER MATERIAL\r\nWHICH IS EITHER A TRADE SECRET OF ANOTHER OR IS PROTECTED BY ANY INTELLECTUAL\r\nPROPERTY, PRIVACY, PUBLICITY, OR OTHER RIGHT, WITHOUT OBTAINING PERMISSION OF\r\nTHE RIGHT HOLDER. </p>\r\n<p>A\r\nUser shall not use any devices or methodology to monitor or copy any web pages\r\nor content found on the Site, without the prior written consent of The Wedding\r\nWebsite Group. A User shall not:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>a. post\r\n     or otherwise distribute any defamatory, obscene or unlawful material or\r\n     information, any information encouraging conduct that would constitute a\r\n     criminal offense or give rise to civil liability, any information or\r\n     software which contains a virus, worm or other harmful or damaging\r\n     component, or any photographs containing obscene images (as determined by\r\n     and in the sole discretion of THE WEDDING WEBSITE GROUP) or unauthorized\r\n     images of another or in which another owns rights, any unauthorized music\r\n     or musical composition or performance;</li>\r\n<li>b.\r\n     defame, harass, threaten or otherwise violate the legal rights of another;\r\n     or</li>\r\n<li>c.\r\n     exploit the Site for any commercial purposes or otherwise use the Site in\r\n     a manner which is contrary to the law of any country or locality.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>4. Privacy Policy</strong></p>\r\n<p>Here\r\nat The Wedding Website Group we are committed to protecting your privacy.</p>\r\n<p>All\r\ninformation on visitors collected by us is used exclusively by The Wedding\r\nWebsite Group and is not otherwise distributed, disclosed, sold, rented, traded\r\nor used for any other purpose. We will only use the information that we collect\r\nabout you lawfully (in accordance with the Data Protection Act 1998). The\r\ninformation is collected by our servers to help us maintain and improve the\r\nwebsite.</p>\r\n<p>The\r\nWedding Website Group may release account information when we believe, in good\r\nfaith, that such release is reasonably necessary to comply with the law or\r\nprotect the rights, property or safety of The Wedding Website Group and our\r\nvisitors.</p>\r\n<p>The\r\nWedding Website Group maintains website information about the number of visits\r\na page receives and technical information used to identify trends but this\r\ninformation is not recorded in such a way that it can be cross referenced to\r\nany specific visitor.</p>\r\n<p>If\r\nyou have any questions, which are not answered here, please feel free to email\r\nus at <a href="mailto:info@worldwidewedding.co.uk">info@worldwidewedding.co.uk</a></p>\r\n<p>The\r\nWedding Website Group reserves the right to change our Privacy Policy. All\r\nchanges will be posted on the site and be effective immediately.</p>\r\n<p><strong>5. User Responsibility.</strong></p>\r\n<p>A\r\nUser is solely responsible for all results of acts or omissions that occur\r\nthrough such User''s actions and for maintaining the confidentiality of any\r\npassword or account information in the User''s control. A USER AGREES TO\r\nINDEMNIFY, DEFEND AND HOLD HARMLESS THE WEDDING WEBSITE GROUP, ITS OWNER(S),\r\nAGENTS, EMPLOYEES, AND CONSULTANTS FROM ANY AND ALL THIRD PARTY CLAIMS,\r\nLIABILITY, DAMAGES AND/OR COSTS (INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, LEGAL FEES)\r\nARISING FROM THE USE OF THE SITE BY USER, THE VIOLATION BY USER OF THIS\r\nAGREEMENT, OR THE INFRINGEMENT BY USER OF ANY RIGHT OF ANOTHER. Users agree to\r\nimmediately notify The Wedding Website Group of any unauthorised use of their\r\naccount or any other breach of security known to them.</p>\r\n<p><strong>6. Uploading Images, Videos or Music</strong></p>\r\n<p>The\r\nusers own all of the content and information posted on The Wedding Website Group,\r\nand you can control how it is shared through your option to password protect\r\nyour website. </p>\r\n<p>Any\r\nmusic, videos and photographs that are uploaded to your wedding website to be\r\ndisplayed on your wedding website are properly licensed for such usage at no\r\ncost to T